  "text": "Having introduced the general setting, it is instrumental to compare it to the framework of local quantum-incoherent operations and classical communication (LQICC) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this framework, Alice can perform arbitrary quantum operations locally, while Bob is restricted to local incoherent operations, and both parties can exchange their measurement outcomes via classical communication, which is provided for free in this setting. In the LQICC scenario entanglement is a more powerful resource than coherence, as via LQICC operations one singlet can be converted into one maximally coherent qubit on Bob's side [CITATION_3] . Without classical communication the situation changes significantly: it is not possible to convert singlets into maximally coherent states on Bob's side if no further communication is provided. However, as we will see in Theorem 1 below, singlets are still useful for local coherence extraction in the presence of an additional quantum channel.",
